Let’s be honest – who here doesn’t love sushi? I could eat it daily although I don’t need or want that much rice every week. Which is why this low-carb, 100% plant-based rainbow cucumber sushi is the perfect compromise! I’ve shared options similar in my story for years but this is awesome! By @alphafoodie

node.text:
Follow @laura_lambe to learn how to transform your physique and still eat your favourite foods. 
 
Can you build a balanced plate like this?! 
 
Plate made by @nataliemelchiorre 
 
📣This is one of the most fundamental steps of eating and nourishing your body to support healthy hormones & menstrual cycles.

A BALANCED PLATE
🥒 1/2 Vegetables (non-starchy & leafy greens)
🐟 1/4 Protein (animal or plant sources)
🌾 1/4 Complex Carb (vegetables, grains, beans, legumes)
🥜 Add on Fat, as needed (nuts, seeds, avocado, coconut, olives, dairy if tolerated)

It's that simple!

What you eat plays a really big role in:
▽ Meeting your macronutrient needs – protein, carbs, fat
▽ Meeting your micronutrient needs – vitamins, minerals, phytonutrients
▽ Reducing inflammation
▽ Balancing blood sugar
▽ Maintaining insulin sensitivity
▽ Supporting hormone metabolism & detoxification

Which all supports your reproductive organs, endocrine system, nervous system, digestive system, immune system, brain health and more...

So that your body feels nourished & safe to ovulate regularly if you have missing or irregular cycles, PCOS, HA, or just came off hormonal birth control...

While producing and metabolizing your hormones in a way that alleviates menstrual symptoms like PMS, PMDD, and heavy or painful periods.

Simple isn't always easy to practice, though, so if you need nutritional support in managing your menstrual symptoms, please reach out! We can talk about how I can support you.

🥞 Who’s feeling this healthy breakfast?! 
 
😍 Bueno Crepes⁣ 
 
This creamy topping combination is beautiful and they are also so easy to make! Put all the ingredients in a blender, blitz and pour it in! So simple yet impressive 😍 ⁣…By @emilygough
⁣
Serves 6  V DF GF RSF⁣
Ingredients:⁣
1 cup rolled oats⁣
1 cup oat milk⁣
2 eggs⁣
1 tsp cinnamon⁣
1 tsp maple syrup⁣
⁣
Toppings:⁣
Mylk chocolate ⁣
Vanilla cashew butter⁣
Bananas ⁣
⁣
Method:⁣
Blend up all the ingredients together in your blender until smooth. ⁣
⁣
Add a scoop on an oiled fry pan and move the pan to evenly coat. Flip and repeat with the remaining batter. ⁣
⁣
Met chocolate and add a little coconut oil to cashew butter if you want it really runny. Drizzle on crepes and add bananas. Enjoy! 
 
#brunch #breakfast #breakfastideas #healthybreakfast

The perfect grilled salmon skewers with a green herb vinaigrette…By @lindseyeats
 
This sauce is tangy, greens galore, garlicky and literally everything I want & more! It serves its purpose as both a marinade for the skewers and served alongside for dipping and drizzlin’.⁠
⁠
Cubed salmon is tossed in a lil olive oil, salt, pepper as well as this vinaigrette made with organic kale & spinach, blended with shallots, garlic, basil & vinegar tossed with the salmon for the skewers.⁠
⁠ 
#salmon #salmonrecipes #grilling #grillingseason⁠

Who’s feeling some chia pudding?! 
 
Creamy coconut chia pudding recipe for 2 ✨
By @vegainsfood 
 
in a bowl or in a jar mix:
4 tbsp (40g) chia seeds
240ml coconut milk (or any plant milk)
1 tbsp sweetener like maple syrup or date sugar
-
Place in the fridge to soak for 40 minutes to 1 hour.
-
I also added fresh fruit, whole grain granola and soy yogurt.

node.text:
Follow @bodysmartfitness for the best fitness tips! 
 
Delicious Parmesan Zucchini Spirals 🙌 Do you say Courgette or Zucchini🥒😄!?!
⠀
Made by @secretsquirrelfood 
 
150 Calories per Spiral :)
⠀
Recipe here:
2 large zucchini
1 tbsp olive oil
1/2 cup panko breadcrumbs
1/2 cup parmesan
1/2 tsp paprika
1/2 tsp pepper
Method:
1. Preheat oven at 200 degrees celsius 
2. Trim ends of zucchini and cut in half
3. Pierce with skewer
4. Hold knife at an angle and cut
5. Twist slowly and continue cutting until the end
6. Spread out the zucchini and drizzle with olive oil
7. Add remaining ingredients in a separate bowl
8. Sprinkle over zucchini and until well covered
9. Bake in oven for 40 mins (turn halfway)
10. Serve with your favourite dipping sauce and enjoy!
